text.tspan: Share of population living in extreme poverty vs. Mean income or
Extreme poverty is defined as living below the International Poverty Line of 1.90 international-$ per day.
Source: World Bank Poverty and Inequality Platform
Note: This data is adjusted for inflation and for differences in the cost of living between countries. It is expressed in international-$ at 2011 prices.
